{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"83134092-eb2c-48f8-a4a9-5dbe66464c1f","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n```bash\ndotnet restore   # pulls updated NuGet packages\ndotnet build     # verify it compiles\ndotnet test      # run your tests\n```\n\nAlso update any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` NuGet references to their 11.x versions. Check the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for anything that affects your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"09a68584-0417-4fd3-8f4f-aa0f07079ac6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward guidance question — I don't need to explore any codebase since there's no repo here. I'll provide concise instructions.","outputTokens":333,"requestId":"7033:1D8045:94BF0A:AAD8F5:69FBEE7C"},"id":"6a095129-ad8d-4dca-8c8a-dd015f41ac3b","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:44:37.255Z","parentId":"f2a885d4-0339-4340-84bb-e01c38fcf6c8"}
